1	// vsim's main RAM must cover QEMU's `virt`-machine RAM base (0x80000000) so
2	// the same ELF can be loaded at the same physical address in both halves of
3	// the hybrid handoff. The cap stays below NDS_HVM_BASE (0x90000000), which
4	// is the CPU's slave-port HVM region; further peripherals (ILM, ACM, AIA,
5	// SMU, UART) start at 0xA0000000+.
6	
